        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 5:13PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 513 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Westwood, or 10 miles northwest of Kalamazoo, moving
east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Kalamazoo...           Portage...             Galesburg...
Parchment...           Climax...              Richland...
Comstock Northwest...  Westwood...            Gull Lake...
Alamo...               Pine Grove...          Augusta...
Gobles...              Oshtemo...             Kendall...
Comstock...            Cooper...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
